description.narrative: UNICEF staff and partners have access to guidance, tools and resources to effectively plan, monitor and evaluate country programme outcomes., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Evaluation And Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children in development and humanitarian setting.

description.narrative: The Philippines Country Office started the first year of the new Country Programme in 2019. The Office took an integrated sectoral approach to planning. Sixteen National 3-year Rolling Workplans (2019-2021), four for Bangsamoro Autonomous Region of Muslim Mindanao, and an Annual Workplan were signed with Government. Three key components of eTools were introduced and are strengthening the link between HACT assurance and Programme Monitoring. Internal audit recommendations have further strengthened Country Office Programme Monitoring | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/02/2020
